RautSoft.econometrics.dataset
Class XYDataset

java.lang.Object
  RautSoft.econometrics.dataset.XYDataset

public class XYDataset
extends java.lang.Object

XYDataset class is the basic data type used for standard Econometric analysis. It is mainly a convenient data type. This class cannot read data from files. However, the constructors of the class can convert a 2-D double array or a Dataset object into XYDataset with the characteristics that the column 0 is the y-variable and rest of the columns are x-variables. If you want to read a dataset from a file and specify the indices of y-variable and x-variables, please create instead a Dataset object using a constructor that reads data from a file and then use the getXYDataset method of that object specifying as paramters ( int yIndex and int[] xIndex).

Example of use:


        double [][] dat ={{10,2,4},{12,2,5},{11,3,2},{15,5,4},{20,6,6}};

        XYDataset data = new XYDataset(dat); //the paramter 3 indicates the number of variables
        // The following four lines are optional
        data.setXLabel(new String[] {"Height", "Food"});
        data.setVName(new String[] {"V2", "V3"});
        data.setYLabel("IQ");
        data.setYName("V1");

        Regress  reg =new Regress(data);
        reg.Compute();
        System.out.println(reg.getOutput() );
        System.out.println(reg.getLogs() );
